# {{.Name}}

A Go library scaffolded with [Forge](https://github.com/reliant-labs/forge).

## Layout

```
{{.Name}}/
├── pkg/{{.Name}}/  # Public API (importable as {{.Module}}/pkg/{{.Name}})
├── internal/        # Private implementation packages
├── docs/            # Architecture Decision Records
├── forge.yaml       # Forge project manifest (kind: library)
├── go.mod
└── Taskfile.yml
```

## Quick start

```bash
task deps   # go mod download
task test   # go test -race ./...
task lint   # golangci-lint run
task fmt    # goimports + go mod tidy
```

## Adding code

- **Public API** lives under `pkg/{{.Name}}/`. Anything you want
  importers to use goes here.
- **Private helpers** live under `internal/`. Use
  `forge add package <name>` to scaffold a new internal package with
  a contract interface and a generated mock.
- **Tests** live next to the code (`xxx_test.go`). Runnable examples
  go into `Example*` test functions; they show up rendered in
  generated docs and run as part of `go test`.

## Versioning

This module follows [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org). Cut
releases by tagging the repository:

```bash
git tag v0.1.0
git push origin v0.1.0
```

Importers will pull the tagged version via `go get {{.Module}}@v0.1.0`.
